      <heading>Wed Feb 23 (Mazrim)     :: \c03The M'Hael's Speech\c00 (2/22/00)</heading>
      <slot>2</slot>
      <level>203</level>
      <author>0</author>
      <date>0</date>
      <text>Asha'man.  Black Tower.  Dumai's Well was your first test, a battle in which 
you have proclaimed to the world and the people living within that you are 
weapons of the highest degree.  A force born out of my guidance and the Lord 
Dragon's desire. A force tried in the midst of battle-blades swinging, blood 
spraying, One Power raging, and death looming. Yet we are victorious. The One 
Power is always victorious, and for that, you should be thankful of your abilities. 
You all know the price; you have before you the choice to attain glory or to fade 
away forever from the annals of history. You are called once more.

Forces of the Shadow have overrun the borderland country of Shienar. Fal 
Moran, its capital city, has been razed and burned to the ground last night.  Men, 
women, children-all dead. Such loss can only be matched by the War of 
Power, the War of Shadow that ended the Age of Legends. They lost their lives 
in defiance of the Shadow. We cannot allow this aggression to go unanswered 
and unchecked, for the possibility of shadowspawn breaking through what 
defenses and fortifications are left between this horde of vermin and our lands is 
just too great. 

A small scouting force, led by the Storm Leader, will Travel to Fal Moran, 
whereupon it will assess the situation before reporting back to me, immediately. 

This is no mere idle threat. You will witness the Shadow firsthand. You will 
come to know why you have trained so hard and have more training yet to come. 
Each of you will become weapons.

For the rest of you, we leave for the Borderlands within the week. Storm Leader 
Gedwyn and Attack Leader Rochaid will be handling squad assignments. See 
the two of them before you resume your training. Dismissed.
</text>
