      <heading>Sat Jan  6 (Ragnar)     :: Captured Aes Sedai</heading>
      <slot>25</slot>
      <level>192</level>
      <author>0</author>
      <date>0</date>
      <text>*written in a scribbled, unlearned hand*
During a patrol in Caemlyn, Soldier Adara, Soldier al'Hael, and myself happened
across a rather distasteful woman in a red dress singing lewd songs in the oval
Plaza.  She slipped in a few verses that were rather degrading towards the
Asha'man, and so I took the paper she was writing her song on in flows of Air
and tossed it out of her hands onto the floor.  She embraced Saidar, and so I
instructed Soldier al'Hael to Shield her, and Soldier Adara to bind her, in
case she could possibly pose a danger to us or any of the citizens around.  As
I did so, a seemingly young woman stepped out of the crowd and demanded I
release the woman in red to her.  Naturally, I refused, and she too embraced
Saidar.  I attempted to shield her twice, and each time, she sliced my flows.
Wishing to end the confrontation quickly, I wove a weak club of Air at her, and
accomplished my goal of knocking her unconcious.  Unfortunately for her, I was
unable to catch her as she fell, as I was distracted by the woman in red.  Who
was struggling against the bonds of Air, as well as the Shield that soldier
al'Hael was maintaining on her.  The woman I had just knocked out fell to the
ground and hit her head rather hard on the floor, causing some moderate
bleeding.  As I was attempting to Heal her, the woman in red managed to break
soldier al'Hael's shield, but he quickly weaved another one.  I saw that I
would be unable to Heal the damage the fall had done to the unconscious woman,
and so I gave the order to release A'lyse, the woman in red.  I carried the
unconscious woman to the Golden Bowl Inn, where I promptly Travelled to the
farm, taking her with me so she could recover and heal.  I am currently keeping
watch over her, but I believe I will transfer that duty to someone else soon.
  
Peace favor your swords
Asha'man Ragnar Karde
</text>
